# Data Layer & Drizzle Standards

## Step 1: Repository Interface
- Define in `src/domain/repositories/[domain].repository.ts`.
- Export a unique string token: `export const DOMINIO_REPOSITORY = 'IDominioRepository';`.
- Include all necessary types (Input, Record, Filter) in this file.

## Step 2: Drizzle Functions
- File: `src/infra/db/[domain]/[action]-[domain].drizzle.ts`.
- Pattern: `export async function actionDomainDb(db: DrizzleClient, data: Input): Promise<Record>`.
- Imports: Tables must come from `../providers/drizzle/config/migrations`.

## Step 3: Service Implementation
- Implement the repository interface in `src/infra/db/[domain]/[domain].service.ts`.
- Inject Drizzle using `@Inject(DRIZZLE_PROVIDER)`.
- Only delegate to drizzle functions; do not write SQL logic inside the Service class.